article.headline: Nebraska 82, SE Louisiana 35
article.story:
LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) -- Three players scored in double figures and
Nebraska held Southeastern Louisiana to just 25 percent shooting
from the field in an 82-25 Cornhusker victory Wednesday night.

Kiera Hardy led the Huskers (5-2) with 14 points. Chelsea Aubry
followed with 11 points and Jina Johansen added 10.

Jessica Gerhart grabbed 11 rebounds for the Huskers as they
outrebounded the Lions (2-1) by more than 30.

Nebraska shot 53 percent from the field and 41 percent from
beyond the 3-point line.

The Lions did not have one player in double figures. Nakeya
Downing led the squad with nine points.
